HEADWORD: Prelatist
<hw>Prel"a*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who supports
of advocates prelacy, or the government of the church by prelates;
hence, a high-churchman.</def> <rj><au>Hume.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am an Episcopalian, but not a <qex>prelatist</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>T. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prelatize</ent>⟦br⟧
